was another telemetry ping \\u2014 something about \'InitialAccess on svc-web from red\'. I don\'t actually manage the web app myself; I just use it to demo the product to prospects. Probably just DevOps doing maintenance. Still, I should drop them a quick line to check if anything odd is going on.\\n  - [ACTION:TALK] to devops@sales-company.com [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: {\\"kind\\":\\"mail\\",\\"service\\":\\"svc-email\\",\\"to\\":\\"devops@sales-company.com\\",\\"subject\\":\\"Quick heads-up on svc-web access\\",\\"body\\":\\"Hi DevOps team,\\\\n\\\\nJust got a network alert mentioning \'InitialAccess on svc-web from red\'. Not my wheelhouse, but flagging in case it\\u2019s unexpected. Demo is on the calendar early tomorrow, so let me know if I should expect any downtime.\\\\n\\\\nThanks!\\\\n-- sales-01\\"\\n  - [ACTION:DONE] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Sent a quick heads-up email to DevOps and waiting for next stimuli.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from sales-02 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Let me open the SaaS console to look at the recent access logs in the mtxConsole.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from engineer-01 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Security team, FYI \\u2013 seeing an InitialAccess beacon from red on svc-web as of now. Looking into the access pattern; will post logs to the ticket shortly.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from finance-01 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Payroll dashboard is on svc-web\\u2014this alert means I can\\u2019t open it until we contain red\\u2019s footprint. Best to stay off that service right now and loop in IT security.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from it_admin-01 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: {\\"kind\\": \\"shell\\", \\"service\\": \\"svc-siem\\", \\"command\\": \\"query alerts --severity HIGH --service svc-web --last 1h --output detailed\\"}\\n  - [ACTION:THINK] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: IT Admin just ran a SIEM query about HIGH severity alerts on svc-web within the last hour. The \\"red\\" footprint seems to be confirmed. I\\u2019m simply a sales rep\\u2014I don\\u2019t know how to read SIEM outputs. All I really care about is whether our demo environment will be stable for tomorrow\\u2019s prospect call. I should let the security folks handle the forensics and focus on finding an alternative demo path or a timeline from them.\\n  - [ACTION:TALK] to it_admin-01 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Thanks for pulling the detailed logs. Anything I should know on timing? I\\u2019ve got a big prospect demo first thing tomorrow that normally runs on svc-web. Let me know if I should move us to the backup cluster or whether you expect containment sooner than that. Happy to reschedule if it keeps everyone safer.\\n  - [ACTION:DONE] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Waiting on IT Admin\\u2019s read-out so I can decide on demo logistics.\\n  - [ACTION:THINK] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: IT Admin just posted the same SIEM query again, probably in response to engineer-01 or as an update for the room. I already saw that red is active on svc-web and already asked him about timing for my demo\\u2014no need to ask twice. I should just watch quietly and see how fast containment will happen.\\n  - [ACTION:DONE] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Waiting to see if IT Admin gives an ETA for cleanup or suggests alternatives for tomorrowu0027s demo.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from it_admin-01 [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: {\\"kind\\": \\"shell\\", \\"service\\": \\"svc-siem\\", \\"command\\": \\"get alerts --severity HIGH --service svc-web --last 1h --format json\\"}\\n  - [ACTION:THINK] [@2026-04-10T00:52:32.774715]: Same SIEM query again from IT Admin \\u2014 seems like they\'re doing parallel checks with engineer-01. I already pinged him about the demo window and he hasn\'t replied with an ETA yet. The safe move now is to quietly set up an alternative plan so I\'m not dead in the water tomorrow. I\'ll fire up the backup demo cluster and test the three core flows we always show (dashboard,